.Dd March 24, 2026
.Dt NT 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm nt
.Nd simple notes maintainer
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Bro Cm h | Cm help Brc
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm n | Cm new Brc Op Ar title
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm l | Cm last Brc Op Ar N
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm li | Cm last-index Brc
.br
.Nm
.Ar num Op Ar ...
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm r | Cm rename Brc Ar num Ar title
.br
.Nm
.Cm rl Ar title
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm rn | Cm renumber Brc Ar n Ar m
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm a | Cm activity Brc
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm ar | Cm activity-recursive Brc
.br
.Nm
.Cm R
.br
.Nm
.Cm t
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility initializes and edits documents, ideal for building an indexed list of notes documents.
.Pp
By default, the file extension for each new document is the extension of the last numbered document in the folder.
If the folder has no numbered documents,
.Nm
defaults to
.Pa .md .
If the folder has a template file
.Ql nt_template. Ns Ar extension ,
then each new document uses this template's content and
.Ar extension .
The template supports the following macros:
.Cm %DATE
is replaced with today's date (yyyy-mm-dd), and
.Cm %TITLE
is replaced with the title passed to
.Cm new .
.Pp
If
.Nm
is given a
.Ar title
when creating or renaming a doc, the delimiter (underscores or hyphens) between the numeric index and the title portion of the file name will match the format of the last doc, defaulting to a single hyphen.
.Pp
As syntactic sugar, you can pass in multiple numeric indices, as well as
.Cm R
and/or
.Cm t
in a row to open the specified files all at once.
.Pp
Title-consuming commands
.Pq Cm n , Cm r , Cm rl
accept an optional hyphen prefix
.Pq e.g., Fl n , Fl r .
Without a hyphen, the command treats all remaining words as the title.
With a hyphen, it stops at the first number or flag, so you can chain
multiple commands on one line:
.Pp
.Dl nt -n my note -3 -r 7 new-title -R
.Pp
creates a note titled
.Dq my note ,
then opens doc 3, renames doc 7, and opens the README \(em all in one go.
Titles containing hyphens or numbers must be quoted when using the hyphen-prefixed form.
.Pp
Options include:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Bro Cm h | Cm help Brc
Print help page.
.It Bro Cm n | Cm new Brc Op Ar title
Create a new document named with the highest unused numeric index (0-padded to 3 digits)
followed by a delimiter and a hyphenated version of the
.Ar title ,
with the same extension as the previous document (or .md), then open it in the preferred editor.
If the current directory contains the file
.Ql nt_template. Ns Ar extension ,
then the new document uses this template's content and
.Ar extension
instead.
.It Bro Cm l | Cm last Brc Op Ar N
Open the document with the latest numeric index.
If
.Ar N
is a positive integer, open the
.Ar N Ns th-to-last
indexed document (1 = last, 2 = second-to-last, etc.).
When using the hyphen-prefixed form, a leading-hyphen next argument is passed on to the next chained command rather than treated as an argument to
.Cm l .
.It Bro Cm li | Cm last-index Brc
Print the numeric index of the last indexed document in the current directory.
.It Ar num Op Ar ...
Open the existing document(s) with the
.Ar num
index (indices).
.It Bro Cm r | Cm rename Brc Ar num Ar title
Rename the existing document with the
.Ar num
index to
.Ar title
without opening the document.
.It Cm rl Ar title
Rename the last indexed document to
.Ar title
without opening the document.
.It Bro Cm rn | Cm renumber Brc Ar n Ar m
Starting from document index
.Ar n ,
renumber the consecutive run of documents so that
.Ar n
becomes
.Ar m ,
.Ar n Ns +1
becomes
.Ar m Ns +1 ,
and so on, until the end of the consecutive sequence.
Documents are renamed in the correct order to avoid collisions.
Fails if any target index is already occupied by a document outside the source range.
.It Bro Cm a | Cm activity Brc
Show an activity summary of indexed documents grouped by last-modified month.
Searches the current directory only.
.It Bro Cm ar | Cm activity-recursive Brc
Show an activity summary of indexed documents grouped by last-modified month.
Searches all subdirectories as well.
.It Cm R
Open the README.md (case-insensitive) document in the current working directory, if there is any.
.It Cm t
Open the
.Pa nt_template
document in the current working directory, if there is any.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ev NT_EDITOR
Highest-priority editor override for
.Nm .
.It Ev VISUAL
Used when
.Ev NT_EDITOR
is not set.
Typically a GUI editor.
.It Ev EDITOR
Used when neither
.Ev NT_EDITOR
nor
.Ev VISUAL
is set.
Typically a terminal editor.
.Pp
If none of the above are set,
.Nm
falls back to
.Xr vim 1 .
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
utility exits with one of the following values:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It 0
Document, either new or existing, was successfully opened.
.It 1
Document, either new or existing, could not be opened.
.It >1
Another error occurred.
.El
